<HEADLINE> Australia Takes on Germany in Malaysia Hockey Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Australia routed South Korea
6-2 in the Azlan Shah Cup on Friday to set up a final against
Germany in the six-nation hockey tournament in Ipoh of Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The Australians wore out the South Korean defence with
lightning attacks. They opened the scoring after five minutes and
led all the way to the end.
</P>
<P>
The final will be the second meeting between Australia and
Germany, who won their first encounter 5-3 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
England drew 1-1 with Malaysia on Friday while Germany, who had
already reached the final, were beaten 3-2 by New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
The Australians top the tournament's standings with 12 points
from five games. Germany have 10 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
