<HEADLINE> BJP, Allies to Work Out National Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP)
and its allies decided Friday to set up a coordinating body and
formulate a national agenda by next Monday for effective
governance.
</P>
<P>
BJP leader Jaswant Singh told reporters after a two-hour
meeting between top leaders of BJP and its allies that those
present were unanimous in having such an agenda which would be
adopted by all the allies before the constitution of the 12th Lok
Sabha on March 12.
</P>
<P>
Singh declined to reveal details of the agenda, saying they
would be made known when the agenda is finalized on Monday.
</P>
<P>
However, another leader of the BJP, Naveen Patnaik, made it
clear that the agenda would not contain any controversial issues.
</P>
<P>
BJP remains India's largest political force following the
just-concluded Lok Sabha elections but failed to win the necessary
majority to form a new government on its own.
</P>
<P>
Its prospects for forming a new government have brightened as
its opponents, the Congress and the United Front, are still
divided over the nature of their collaboration.  
</P>
</TEXT>
