<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Streamline Family Planning Program: Abida </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government will
streamline its family planning program to spur prosperity in the
country, Minister for Population Welfare Syed Abida Hussain said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a seminar on the "Preliminary Findings of Pakistan
Fertility Planning Society Survey 1996-97," Abida said the
public's response to the family planning program is "encouraging."
</P>
<P>
Abida called on those engaged in family planning services to
work with passion to create awareness among the public in this
respect.
</P>
<P>
Without checking over-population, Abida said, it is impossible
to ensure the provision of education, health, information and
communication facilities to people and enable them to enjoy a
happy life.
</P>
<P>
She called on the people to have a small family and urged the
promotion of education, especially for women.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was organized by the National Institute of
Population Studies, according to the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan now has a high population growth rate of about 2.7
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
