<HEADLINE> Steel Production Up Further in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany's steel production continued
to rise last month, with crude steel output reaching 3.77 million
tons, up 9.9 percent from February 1997, said reports reaching
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The steel output in western Germany grew by 7.5 percent to 3.29
tons, while that in the eastern area came to 0.48 tons, up
30.8 percent, said the Duesseldorf-based steel industry branch of
the Federal Statistics Office.
</P>
<P>
The office also reported that Germany's pig iron output reached
2.57 million tons in February, an increase of 8.6 percent over
the same period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
