<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Sends Message for Women's Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 6 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Friday called for solidarity to protect women's rights
which he said are the responsibility of all humankind.
</P>
<P>
In his message for International Womens's Day which falls on
March 8, Annan said gender-based abuses reflect the inequalities
that women face in their everyday lives.
</P>
<P>
"Gender equality is not only a goal in itself, it is a means to
meeting the challenge of reduing poverty, promoting sustainable
development and building good governance," he said.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief calls attention to the plight of women in
countries experiencing armed conflict as women and children there
are particularly likely to suffer. 
</P>
