<HEADLINE> Contact Group Meeting to Send Tough Message to Milosevic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 6 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook said Friday that the Contact Group meeting on Kosovo issue
due to be held in London Monday will send a tough-minded message
to Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic.
</P>
<P>
Cook, whose country is the current European Union (EU)
president, said in a statement issued Friday afternoon that the
crisis in Kosovo is deepening with incoming reports of further
repressive violence by the Serbian military police.
</P>
<P>
Cook noted that he had sent British Ambassador in Belgrade to
Kosovo with his Contact Group colleagues "to make first hand
assessment of the situation."
</P>
<P>
On the Contact Group conference in London, Cook said that the
meeting the group -- including Russia, the United States, France,
Germany, Britain and Italy -- would urge Yugoslav President
Milosevic to resolve the current crisis peacefully.
</P>
<P>
"I expect it to be a tough-minded meeting, concentrating on how
to bring home to President Milosevic the need for an immediate end
to repressive action," Cook said.
</P>
<P>
"We will take full account of the implications of the crisis in
Kosovo for the region and in particular for Albania and the former
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia," He added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
