<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 120 Hutu Insurgents Killed in Central Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Rwandan army has killed about
120 armed bandits in central Gitarama Prefecture, state-run Radio
Rwanda announced Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Commander of the Gitarama Brigade, Karenzi Karake, had
confirmed the information.
</P>
<P>
According to Karake, the Rwandan army lost eight soldiers,
including one officer, while 12 others sustained injuries.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he denied media reports saying that the above
officer was brutally killed by the insurgents who decapitated
him.
</P>
<P>
Since Saturday last week, the Rwandan army is pitted against
armed insurgents who attacked three communes north of Gitarama
town from their harbor in northwestern Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
The three communes where security was disturbed are
Nyakabanda, Bulinga and Rutobwe, north of Gitarama town.
</P>
<P>
Mopping-up operations to dislodge the enemy from some hills of
the Ndiza region were continuing on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
However, military sources in Gitarama indicated that it will
not take long to have the militiamencompletely rooted out of
that region.
</P>
<P>
It is said that Saturday's attack was triggered by the intense
military and logistical pressure the Hutu insurgents are faced
with in northwestern Rwanda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
