<HEADLINE> Former Cypriot President Appointed Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot cabinet Friday formally
appointed George Vassiliou, the former president, to head the
Republic's delegation that will negotiate membership to the
European Union (EU), the government spokesman announced.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after a cabinet meeting, Spokesman Christos
Stylianides Vassiliou will have the right to participate meetings
and submit suggestions concerning the accession negotiations, but
he is not empowered to make commitment.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Vassiliou, former Cypriot president from
1988-1993, will be kept informed by cabinet members about
government efforts to align the country's legislation with that
of the EU.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus submitted its application for full EU membership in
1990. The EU summit last December decided to start accession
negotiations with the Cypriot government on March 31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
