<HEADLINE> UK New Car Sales Rise 8.3 pct in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 6 (Xinhua) -- New car sales in Britain continued
rising last month, up 8.3 percent over the same period last year,
after a more than 12 percent increase in January, according to
figures from the Society of Motor Manufacturers and Traders (SMMT)
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The SMMT said that the two strong months have lifted sales to
more than 10 percent above the same period last year and pointed
to another buoyant year for car sales.
</P>
<P>
The society attributed the rise to an exceptionally competitive
market and significant new models being introduced.
</P>
<P>
Imports kept on rising and accounted for 67.7 percent of sales,
compared with 65.4 percent a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Among the manufacturers, Chrysler Jeep's sale rose 59 percent,
BMW up 33 percent and Nissan up more than 31 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
