<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 18:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cooperation Urged Among European Stock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- European stock exchanges were
urged Friday to cooperate among them to face tougher and more
complex competitive conditions.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening of a European Stock Exchanges Forum
here, Cypriot Finance Minister Christodoulos Christodoulou
stressed the need for cooperation among national stock exchanges,
given the globalization of the securities market, which leads to
tougher and more complex competitive conditions.
</P>
<P>
The one-day forum, held by the Federation of European Stock
Exchanges and participated by some 30 bourses in European
countries, mainly deals with the issue of emerging markets.
</P>
<P>
Christodoulou also said the meeting is indicative of Cyprus'
interest in building up close relations and cooperation among the
stock exchange authorities of European countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that given the openness of the people of Cyprus and the
island's forthcoming accession to the European Union, it is not
surprising that the two-year-old Cyprus Stock Exchange (CSE) has
already begun to develop its relationship with Europe.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the recent measures announced by the Cypriot
government to boost the stock market in Cyprus, Christodoulou
said that the long-term development of any securities market must
be based on sound legislative and operational fundamentals.
</P>
<P>
In view of this reality, he added, the Cypriot government has
given emphasis to the establishment of appropriate legal and
operational framework that will ensure investors' confidence and
market transparency.
</P>
<P>
CSE Chairman Dinos Papadopoulos also stressed at the meeting
that one of the CSE objectives is to play an important role in
the strategy to further develop Cyprus as a regional business
center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
