<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Says He Has Full Confidence in China's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region Tung Chee Hwa, who arrived back
after attending the opening session of the Ninth National People's
Congress in Beijing, said Friday that he was fully confident about
China's future.
</P>
<P>
Tung said he was delighted to attend the opening session on
Thursday and hear the government work report delivered by Premier
Li Peng, acquainting himself with achievements his country has
made in all areas over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
He said China has developed very well, which provides enormous
support to Hong Kong in the wake of the financial turmoil in Asia.
</P>
<P>
While his stay in Beijing was short, arrangements were made for
him to meet with President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng and Vice
Premiers Zhu Rongji and Qian Qichen on separate occasions, Tung
said.
</P>
<P>
They all expressed concern over the grave challenges faced by
Hong Kong in the financial turmoil, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they showed full confidence in Hong Kong's ability
to cope with the financial crisis and spoke highly of the SAR
government's handling of the matter, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
They again pledged the central government's support to the SAR
if it is needed and reiterated their resolve to carry out the
principle of "one country, two systems" in Hong Kong, Tung added.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
