<HEADLINE> 3 Pro-Israeli Soldiers, Boy Wounded in South </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Three Israeli-backed South Lebanese
Army (SLA) soldiers and an innocent boy were wounded in
guerrillas' clashes with Israeli troops and SLA in south Lebanon
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Local Orient Radio said that an SLA member was wounded when
guerrillas detonated a bomb near the SLA post at the village of
Hadais in the western sector of the Israeli-occupied south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place at 1:00 pm local time (1100GMT) when
the SLA members were changing shifts, the radio added.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese security sources said they saw several missiles
landing near the village in suspected Israeli retaliation for
guerrilla's attacks.
</P>
<P>
In the morning at the village of Mashgala in the western
sector of the zone, a boy was wounded under the Israeli
fire. Several cars of civilians were also damaged.
</P>
<P>
In another development, two SLA members were wounded during
five offensives launched by guerrillas in the SLA-controlled
Jezzine, just north of the occupied zone, according to the radio.
</P>
<P>
Since Israel occupied a 1,200-square-kilometer area in south
Lebanon in 1985 as a buffer zone with the aim of preventing
guerrillas' cross-border attack from its north, the tit-for-tat
clashes between them have occurred almost everyday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
