<HEADLINE> Turkey to Participate in NATO Drills in Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Air Forces will
participate in the NATO manoeuvres in Portugal from March 9 to 21
with 16 F-16 fighters and 41 personnel, the semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, codenamed "Strong Resolve '98", is bound to be
held in the Monte Real air base in Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Troops from Germany, Belgium, the Netherlands, France, Britain,
Italy, Spain, Portugal, Greece and the United States will also
participate in the manoeuvres.
</P>
<P>
Military officials from these countries will exchange
information during the exercises.
</P>
<P>
Greece has announced that it will not allow Turkish military
jets to fly to Portugal over its air space, Turkish military
sources were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Greece, both members of the NATO and historical
rivals, have always refrained from meeting each other in NATO
military exercises.
</P>
<P>
The two neighboring countries have been at odds over the
limits of air space, sea-bed mineral resources, sovereignty over
islets in the Aegean as well as the Cyprus issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
