<HEADLINE> NPC and CPPCC Sessions Continue Discussing Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Over the past several days,
participants in the first sessions of China's supreme organ of
state power and leading advisory body have been discussing a
government work report and three other reports.
</P>
<P>
About 5,000 deputies to the Ninth National People's Congress
(NPC) and members of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) heard and
discussed the reports.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan,
Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing have joined some NPC and
CPPCC groups in discussions on reform of state-owned enterprises,
reemployment of laid-off workers, strengthening the fundamental
role of agriculture, revitalizing the country with science and
technology, sustainable economic development and institutional
restructuring of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Most NPC deputies and CPPCC National Committee members regard
the government work report as "pragmatic" and "inspiring", saying
achievements made over the last five years, as summed up by the
report, have laid a good foundation for the country's
trans-century development.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, problems mentioned in the report demonstrate
that the Chinese leadership has remained sober-minded.
</P>
<P>
On March 6, the NPC deputies and CPPCC members heard reports on
national social and economic development, the country's finances,
and institutional restructuring of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the deputies and members hold the view that the
intensity of institutional restructuring this time surpasses all
previous programs.
</P>
<P>
They said institutional restructuring is the pressing need of
economic restructuring and is conducive to economic and social
development. They expressed the hope that reform measures can be
carried out as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
In the coming two days, the participants will continue to
discuss these reports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
