<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- A senior women official today
called for the whole society to show solicitude for laid-off
female workers on the eve of the International Women's Day, which
falls on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He Luli, vice-chairperson of the All-China Federation of Women,
said that female workers used to be in a disadvantageous position
in finding jobs as compared with men. The government and all
social sectors should offer them assistance in this respect.
</P>
<P>
Though women in China have long ago acquired an equal status
with men, there are still more illiterate women than men. And
poor educational background makes it more difficult for the women
laid0ffs to get new jobs.
</P>
<P>
Many work units are reluctant to recruit female graduates or
laid-offs, she said, adding that women should on no account be
discriminated against.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, she urged the Chinese women to give full play to
their advantages in employment and asked women's federations at
all levels to come to their aid.  
