<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, March 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi Foreign Minister Mohammed Saeed al-Sahhaf left
here Saturday for New York to hold talks with
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan, the Iraqi News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi delegation will discuss with Annan the steps to be
taken regarding the increase of oil Iraq is allowed to sell under
the U.N.-Iraq oil-for-food deal. (Iraq-Annan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- China's central bank governor said that maintaining
a stable RMB value is not the personal will of Chinese leaders,
but a reflection of both supply and demand on the exchange market
and overall performance of the Chinese economy.
(China-Currency-Stability)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Latvia defended Saturday the dispersing of a rally of
Russian-speaking protesters in front of City Duma in Riga by
Latvian police on March 3 as "a legal and self-defense act."
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Ziedonis Cevers told an extraordinary meeting
of the cabinet that the police acted "within the bounds of the
law," the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The police used batons only for the purpose of self-defense,
Cevers said, adding that they "have the legitimate right to use
this special means for self-defense in such situations."
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Latvian police pushed and dispersed a group of
mostly elderly Russian-speakers protesting against the high cost
of living. (Russia-Latvia-Protest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Belarussian President Alexandr Lukashenko arrived
here Friday night for an official visit to Iran, the Iranian
official news agency IRNA reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking upon his arrival, Lukashenko said that during his
visit to Iran no specific issue would be discussed and no measure
would be taken against a third country.
</P>
<P>
Announcing Minsk's readiness for cooperation with Tehran, he
said that Belarus is an independent state and has the right to
establish relations with an independent country such as
Iran. (Iran-Belarus-Visit) 
</P>
