<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BJP Leader Appeals for unity in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Atal Beharl Vajpayee, former
Indian prime minister and leader of the Bharatiya Janata Party
(BJP), tried to allay fears among other sections following his
election as BJP leader in the parliament Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"We are now about to get an opportunity at the center. There
should be no apprehensions about BJP in anyone's mind," Vajpayee
said in his address to the newly elected parliamentarians from his
party .
</P>
<P>
Recalling his resolution expressed during the debate on the
motion of confidence of his short-lived government in 1996 that he
would come back with adequate votes, the prime ministerial
candidate said that the party has now returned with more support.
</P>
<P>
BJP and its allies have secured 257 out of the 535 contested
seats in the first three phases of the four-phase elections to the
Lok Sabha, the Lower House of Parliament, but failed to pass the
crucial figure of 273 seats to form a new government.
</P>
<P>
The 72-year-old veteran politician said that the BJP has now
reached each and every corner of the country both geographically
and socially.
</P>
<P>
It is not because the BJP did not have people's support but
might be due to inadequate effort on its own part, he explained,
adding that the party would have to take the support of allies.
</P>
<P>
The BJP and its allies decided on Friday to reduce the areas of
conflict and keep all contentious issues out of a national agenda
to be drafted by a coordination committee set up on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The contentious issues include abrogation of Article 370 of the
Constitution, construction of a Ram temple and introduction of a
uniform civil code.
</P>
<P>
During consultations with leaders of the poll-partners over the
past few days, Vajpayee is said to have made it clear that faced
with the challenge of running a government with an uncertain
majority, it would be fatal to pursue any conflict agenda.
</P>
<P>
Maintaining hate was not on BJP agenda, he told the BJP
parliamentary group Saturday, saying that his government would
ensure security, prosperity and happiness of all sections.
</P>
<P>
"We don't consider different religions as obstacles but as
symbols of our cultural richness and that which represented unity
in diversity. We should take them all together," Vajpayee said.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to all political parties to play a constructive
role in evolving a consensus to tackle major issues facing the
nation.
</P>
<P>
Now that elections were nearly over, it was time to get down to
work and set aside the war of words which all parties had indulged
in during the elections, he said.
</P>
<P>
Vajpayee assured that a BJP government under his leadership
would fulfill the aspirations of the people on the basis of a
national agenda being worked out by the BJP and its allies.
</P>
<P>
In politics, he said, the opposition can not be considered as
an enemy but as one with whom there were differences of view
points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
