<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills Two People in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 7 (Xinhua) -- A 4-year-old girl and a young man
were killed on the spot and 35 others were injured in a road
accident Saturday morning on the Dhaka-Chittagong Highway, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at about 10 am local time when a bus from
Dhaka collided head-on with a Dhaka-bound bus from Comilla, at
Bhitikandi in the Munshiganj district, about 30 kilometers
southeast of the capital.
</P>
<P>
The first bus skidded off the road and rolled over into a
roadside ditch, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Nine seriously injured persons were rushed to Dhaka hospitals
while the rest were given medial treatment at a local health
complex.
</P>
<P>
The boys and girls from a kindergarten of Comilla, 90
kilometers southeast of here, were traveling to visit the Mirpur
zoo in Dhaka.
</P>
