<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese Province Promoting Forest Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Forests in China's Hebei
Province had 2.75 million tourists in 1997, providing 40 million
yuan in profits.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has used its abundant forest resources for tourism and
put over 76 million yuan into forest parks in 1997, having gotten
10 million from foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government also has preferential policies for
them and has built 46 provincial-level forest parks on 240,000
hectares of land.
</P>
<P>
Most were built on forest farms with poor facilities and
they've allocated money for updating facities and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Xibaipo Park put 13 million yuan into five scenic spots in 1996
and 1997, and now has 50,000 tourists annually.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has 60,000 people working in forest tourism and has
provided formal training to improve their service level. 
</P>
