<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Calls for Use of More Competent Personnel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- The reforms of the state-owned
enterprises and government institutions will prompt personnel
structure to be improved and more competent people to be tapped
and used.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing made the remark while speaking at a
panel discussion of deputies from east China's Jiangsu Province,
who are here attending the ongoing First Session of the Ninth
People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
The reforms will divert some people to other posts, the
vice-premier said, and it will provide an opportunity to readjust
the personnel mix and raise the quality of people.
</P>
<P>
"We should make concerted efforts to tackle the problem so as
to lay a good foundation for future development," he said.
</P>
<P>
On revitalizing the country with science and education, Li said
more efforts should be made to facilitate the shift from the type
of examination-oriented education to the one that stresses the
students' quality development, Li said.
</P>
<P>
More money will be spent to cope with difficulties and problems
existing in the working and living conditions of teachers, young
teachers in particular, he said. 
</P>
