<HEADLINE> NGOs Urged to Raise Awareness About Violence Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Women organizations and Non-
Governmental Organizations (NGOs) in Pakistan have been urged to
raise awareness of people about the issue of violence against
women.
</P>
<P>
These organizations should maintain unity among their ranks and
collectively fight against the menace of violence against women,
said Begum Tehmina Daultana, Minister of State for Women
Development, Social Welfare and Special Education, while
inaugurating a three-day photo exhibition on "Violence Against
Girls and Women in South Asia: Prospects for Change" held here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Tehmina noted that violence against women is an obstacle to
achieve the objectives of equality, development and peace.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani government has been committed to eliminate evils
such as violence against women from the society, she said.
</P>
<P>
She said that two crisis prevention centers have been set up in
the country to help address grievances of those poor women who by
anyway are victimized.
</P>
<P>
The government plans to set up more crisis prevention centers
in various cities throughout the country with the help of NGOs,
she added.
</P>
<P>
The photo exhibition is organized by the Ministry of Women
Development, Social Welfare and Special Education in collaboration
with the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF). It will
continue till March 10, according to the Associated Press of
Pakistan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
