<HEADLINE> Construction Bank to Help Ease Private Housing Woes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, March 7 (Xinhua) -- The Construction Bank of China
plans to grant mortgage loans of over 30 billion yuan to help
ordinary Chinese citizens purchase housing.
</P>
<P>
The projected loan volume is slightly less than total loans the
bank has granted to individuals since the 1980s, according to
information released by a bank official during a recent seminar held
in Changsha, capital of central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
Housing loans were previously limited to people working for
either state institutions or companies. However, loans for this
year will be granted to anyone with sufficient personal assets and
the capacity to make loan and interest payments, according to the
official.
</P>
<P>
Bank loans of some 490 million yuan have already provided over
12,000 Hunan families with an opportunity to purchase new
homes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
