<DOCNO> XIE19980307.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Ethnic Region Experiencing Good Time for Rural Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, March 7 (Xinhua) -- China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region has entered a good period for its rural economy, with the
regional government giving priority to agriculture in its
development plans.
</P>
<P>
The region, in northwestern China, produced 2.5 billion kg of
grain on nearly 800,000 ha in 1997, the same as the previous
year's record high.
</P>
<P>
It also had big increases in the amount of meat, eggs, milk,
vegetables, fruits, and aquatic products. Township and village
enterprises reported nine billion yuan in output value last year,
up 27 percent, and accounting for 70 percent of the region's rural
production. Farmers per-capita income amounted to 1,580 yuan in
1997.
</P>
<P>
The number of poverty-stricken people in the southern
mountainous area is down from 69 percent to 25 percent of the
total population.
</P>
<P>
For the past five years, Ningxia has increased spending on
agriculture by more than 10 percent and established grain, dairy,
sugar beet, vegetable, beer, fruit, meat, and fur production
centers and 140 enterprises to process these goods.
</P>
<P>
The region has also developed 640 agriculture industrialization
organizations, which did 6.5 billion yuan in business last year
and helped the industrial and service sectors in rural areas make
up nearly 50 percent of the economy.
</P>
<P>
Agronomy also played a role. The southern mountainous area used
plastic sheeting on more than 30,000 ha of corn last year, which
increased grain output by some 20 million kg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980307.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Increase Capital Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese top banker announced here
today that China will increase fixed assest investment by 270
billion yuan (32.5 billion US dollars) in 1998, a rise of more
than 10 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
Dai Xianglong, governor of the Peoplel's Bank of China, said
the plan is launched to guarantee the attainment of the government
growth target of eight percent for this year.
</P>
<P>
"While we don't abandon the appropriately tight monetary
policy, we should increase money supply properly, the investment
in fixed assets in particular, so as to guarantee that the
economic targets are met," said Dai at a press conference hosted
by the on-going NPC session here today.
</P>
<P>
In face of the recent Southeast Asia financial turmoil, there
is all the more impressing need for China to develop the internal
market and expanding domestic demand as well, he noted.
</P>
<P>
China has a high saving rate, with the national deposit pool
expanding by some 800 billion yuan (96.4 billion US dollars)
annually. "Therefore conditions are available for increasing
investment," Dai said.
</P>
<P>
Beginning this year, the central bank has removed lending
quotas imposed on the state banks, which are allowed to make loan
decisions on their own but have to be held responsible for their
profitability.
</P>
<P>
As banks are granted more autonomy, the actual investment is
very likely to exceed the planned figure, Dai said.
</P>
<P>
According to the top banker, investment priority will be given
to leading infrastructure projects, such as railway, highway,
municipal works, environment improvement and private housing
projects.
</P>
<P>
"Financing of the projects under construction and Sino-foreign
joint venture projects already approved will be accelerated and
new projects that have passed feasibility studies will also get
funding support," Dai said.
</P>
<P>
As part of the effort to beef up the lending strength of the
state banks, he noted, the Ministry of Finance planed to grant
them special treasury bonds and, more important, the central bank
has projected to cut the compulsory minimum reserve ratio from
current 13 percent to 8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Residential housing is another area to get the full bank
support. Dai revealed that the loan for private housing
construction will reach between 100 billion yuan (12 billion US
dollars) and 150 billion yuan (18 US dollars), doubling that of
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the focus will be shifted from private housing
development to expanding the scope of mortgage loans, so as to
enable more people to afford their own houses, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We will prohibit to divert the funding for building luxury
hotels, high-grade office buildings and villas so as to prevent a
possible resurgence of a new round of bubble economy," Dai noted.
</P>
<P>
To further increase the strength and lending capacity of the
state banks, the Ministry of Finance is going to issue special
treasury bonds, and the central bank has also projected to cut the
compulsory minimum reserve ratio from current 13 percent to 8
percent, the central bank governor said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
