<HEADLINE> Japan Takes Dynasty Cup Despite Bowing to China 2-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 7 (Xinhua) -- China snapped hosts Japan's unbeaten
record with a surprising 2-0 victory on Saturday, but Japan still
managed to lift the Dynasty Cup for the third straight time by
dint of a better goal difference.
</P>
<P>
Forward Li Bing opened the score five minutes into the game and
added the second at the 51st minute in the second half.
</P>
<P>
China's defenders kept Japanese playmaker Hidetoshi Nakata
close in check for their second victory against one loss in the
four-team East Asian triennial football tournament.
</P>
<P>
South Korea, the other World Cup qualifier from Asia, barely
saved face as Choi Yong-Soo headed home in injury time for a 1-0
win over unfancied Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
Japan, China and South Korea finished the round robin with two
wins and one loss each. Hong Kong ended up at the bottom with
three straight defeats.
</P>
<P>
But the hosts, who mauled Hong Kong, China 5-1 in an earlier
match, finished atop with a goal difference of three, against two
for China and one for South Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
