<HEADLINE> 77,286 Ethiopian Female Civil Servants Benefit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Civil Service
Commission has announced that the new regulation on maternity
leave will benefit about 77,286 female civil servants.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency on Saturday, the
announcement was made after the federal government adopted the
new regulation on maternity leave which gives every woman a
30-day holiday before and a 60-day leave after childbirth.
</P>
<P>
The commission said the new regulation will support efforts
underway to ensure the rights of female civil servants promoting
mother-child health care and raising their productivity.
</P>
<P>
It also permits additional days off duty upon instructions by
an authorized physician of any sickness a woman faces in the pre
and post natal period, the commission said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the new maternity leave regulation is one which
provides practical response to an international declaration on
women's rights Ethiopia has ratified. 
</P>
</TEXT>
