<HEADLINE> General Motors Projects Doing Well in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Shanghai
General Motors Co. Ltd., a major Sino-US venture involving
investments of 1.52 billion US dollars, is proceeding smoothly,
with the initial output of Buick sedans expected to roll-off the
assembly line by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the venture held a meeting today and pledged to
ensure timely completion of the project and smooth operations
thereafter. Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo sent a congratulatory
telegram supporting the effort.
</P>
<P>
The State Council approved the project on January 10 last year,
with construction beginning on the very same day. A new
state-of-the-art automobile manufacturing base is currently taking
shape in the city.
</P>
<P>
The project, listed as one of Shanghai's key projects in 1998,
is a joint effort being carried out by the Shanghai Automobile
Manufacturing Corp. and U,S.-based General Motors Corp. (GMC).
</P>
