<HEADLINE> China to Start International Mail-Order Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- China's Posts and
Telecommunications departments are working with their
U.S. counterparts to establish a Global Package Link Service for
the Chinese market, including Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The service will enable Chinese consumers to order and purchase
commodities listed in the international market without the need to
travel abroad, according to recent edition of International Trade
News.
</P>
<P>
The service will initially be offered in Shanghai, China's
largest metropolitan area, and later in various other major
cities, including Beijing and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper called the service a result from the strategic
cooperation between the postal services of China and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
In addition, similar services between China and Japan and
Russia are currently under negotiation. 
</P>
