<HEADLINE> Calm Returns to Central Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Calm has returned in the communes
of Central Gitarama where security has been seriously disturbed
this week, officials in Gitarama prefecture have indicated.
</P>
<P>
"Although there has been some disruption, life has returned to
normal," the Deputy Commander of the Gitarama -Kibuye Brigade,
Cot Karenzi Karake said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He, however, indicated that mop up operations were continuing
in some communes to crash the last "Interahamwe" militiamen
scattered in forests, hills, and swamps of Ndiza region, a
special story from Rwandan News Agency reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Karake also gave details of Thursday's fighting at Cyuvi and
Shori hills, on the border between Bulinga and Rutobwe communes.
</P>
<P>
"The army killed 18 infiltrators, and seized four assault
rifles, " Karenzi Karake told RNA.
</P>
<P>
The army is said to have sustained four casualties.
</P>
<P>
It is also said that some of the 80 prisoners of common crimes
who had been released in Nyakabanda last Saturday have started to
return.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the militiamen behind the insecurity north of
Gitarama town have been cut off from returning to where they
attacked from, in southern Gisenyi and Ruhengeri Prefectures.
</P>
</TEXT>
