<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Telephones Help People Escape Poverty in Gansu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 7 (Xinhua) -- The telephone, which is a
common instrument in major cities of today's China, has special
significance to people in northwest China's Gansu Province. For
them, it provides one way to a well-off life.
</P>
<P>
Kang Kegui in Kangjiaya, a county known for its poverty, said
he has become wealthy by using a telephone, which has allowed him
to contact his customers more easily.
</P>
<P>
"In the sales prime time, my telephone fees are always over
10,000 yuan per month," Kang said. He is a potato dealer. Every
year, he sells 50,000 tons of potatoes.
</P>
<P>
In other impoverished areas in Gansu such as Dingxi, Longnan
and Tianshui, telephones were put in the most eye-catching places
and in families who needed phones for business purposes.
</P>
<P>
About 150,000 telephone subscribers sign up every year in
Gansu. To meet the growing need, the provincial government puts
more than 1 billion yuan into telecommunications construction per
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
