<HEADLINE> Uganda Radio Wins UNESCO Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Voice of Tooro (VOT), a local
Uganda radio, won an UNESCO award of 20,000 U.S. dollars for its
activities in rural communication, The New Vision reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The award was established by the executive board of UNESCO at
its 120 session recently.
</P>
