<HEADLINE> China's Govt Institutions Restructuring Significant: HK Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong newspapers Saturday
hailed the central government's institutional restructuring
program as being of far-reaching importance.
</P>
<P>
The restructuring plan under which the government's ministries
and commissions will be slashed from 40 down to 29 was explained
by Luo Gan, state councilor and secretary-general of the State
Council, at the First Session of the Ninth National People's
Congress on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Wen Wei Po said in its editorial Saturday that the
restructuring plan has taken into account both the needs of
China's reform and development, and the burden that the society
can bear.
</P>
<P>
The editorial noted that China is simultaneously facing grave
challenges and good chances for development. The trend for
international financial and economic integration and lessons from
financial turmoil in Asia has demonstrated that the establishment
of a highly efficient, well coordinated and standardized
administrative system which separates functions of the government
from those of the enterprise will play an important role in
maintaining China's economic growth, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
Ta Kung Pao in a commentary Saturday described the
institutional restructuring of the State Council as "a
revolution," saying restructuring of government institutions is
urgently needed to deepen economic reform and promote economic and
social development.
</P>
<P>
It is also a necessity in bringing the government closer to the
people, the daily said, adding this will surely bring benefits
by promoting the market economy and attracting foreign
investments.
</P>
<P>
A commentary carried by The Hong Kong Commercial Daily Saturday
said the restructuring of the institutions shows the government's
determination to implement the principle of governing the state
and exercising administration by rule of law.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong people warmly welcome the plan because it was
worked out after summing up the historical experience and
earnestly considering the social needs, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The improvement of a socialist legal system will provide a
powerful guarantee for the implementation of the principle of "one
country, two systems" in Hong Kong, the commentary said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
