<HEADLINE> George Rewrite World Indoor Pole Vault Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Emma George of Australia became
the third woman in a week to break the world indoor record for
pole vault when she cleared 4.47 meters at the Adelaide indoor
athletics classic on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
George, who improved her own outdoor world record in New
Zealand two weeks ago, added the indoor record when she cleared
the mark at her first attempt.
</P>
<P>
She beat the previous mark of 4.46 set by Daniela Bartova of
the Czech Republic in Berlin less than 24 hours earlier.
</P>
<P>
Bartova had in turn beaten the mark of 4.45 set by Anzhela
Balakhonova of the Ukraine at the European indoor championships in
Valencia on March 1.
</P>
<P>
George set an outdoor record of 4.57 meters in Auckland a
fortnight ago, improving her own mark by one centimeter. 
</P>
