<HEADLINE> Uganda Airlines to Sell Its Shares in ENHAS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Uganda Airlines is ready to sell
its shares in Entebbe Handling Services Limited (ENHAS), The New
Vision reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to top aviation sources yesterday, the state
enterprise is in a desperate need for capital to resuscitate its
operation. Uganda Airlines wants some three billion Uganda
Shillings (some three million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
ENHAS was formed in 1994 to activise the services for handling
visitors and break the monopoly of Uganda Airlines in the
services. ENHAS is a profit earning enterprise. Uganda Airlines
have 50 percent of shares of ENHAS.
</P>
<P>
Majority shareholders of ENHAS showed their interest in buying
the shares. The privatisation unit of the country is arranging
the sale, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Uganda Airlines itself is one of the state enterprises to be
privatised by the end of 2,000 year. Uganda has a plan to
privatise its big state enterprises such as Uganda Electrocity
Board, National Water and Sewerage Corporation. The country has
already sold part of its shares in Uganda Commercial Bank.
</P>
