<HEADLINE> Premier Calls for Improved Farming Techniques and More Input </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng today called on
local governments to maintain sober-minded about the weakness of
agriculture in the national economy though farming production
scored great progress over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng made the appeal while joining in a penal discussion by
members of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
During the discussion, 16 CPPCC National Committee members, who
are here for the First Session of the CPPCC Ninth National
Committee, made speeches concerning agrotechnical advances,
protecting grain production and forests, improving water
conservation, mechanizing farm work, and alleviating the burden on
farmers.
</P>
<P>
After hearing the speeches with a meticulous care, Li said that
the growth of agriculture depends on stable policy, more input and
still better use of science and technology.
</P>
<P>
"We should stabilize the household responsibility system with
renumeration linked to output. This is decided by China's present
realities," he said, adding that the initiative of farmers must be
protected.
</P>
<P>
Science and technology are vital factors that contribute to the
increase in agricultural production over the past several years,
but the rate of contribution lags far behind that in developed
nations, the premier noted.
</P>
<P>
In this sense, he urged local officials to spare no effort to
publicize latest and effective farming techniques, such as using
chemical fertilizer and plastic film sheets and applying fine
strains in a still more scientific way.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Premier Li Peng voiced agreement with the CPPCC
National Committee members in the view that more funds should be
allocated in agriculture, saying that apart from government input,
rural collective units, individual farmers and other sectors of
society should encouraged to invest more in agricultural
production.  
</P>
</TEXT>
