<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji on Institutional Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji today
urged leading officials at all levels to fully realize the urgency
and importance of institutional restructuring and spare no effort
in making the forthcoming government reform a success.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, also a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
of the Communist Party of China's Central Committee, made the
remark during a group discussion this morning with deputies to the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC),in session here since last
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Accelerating government restructuring is urgently needed in
the process of establishing a socialist market economy, and it is
also a common wish of the Party and people," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
Party and government leaders across the country must reach a
real common understanding, and earnestly carry out the government
reform with confidence, a high sense of responsibility and
discipline, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Only by so doing can we attain the goal of downsizing the
government, improving officials' competence and strengthening the
management of enterprises, and improve government work to a new
level," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also heard the legislators' opinions on a government work
report delivered earlier by Premier Li Peng at the ongoing NPC
session and on issues of reform of state-owned enterprises,
re-employment of laid-off workers and agricultural development.
</P>
</TEXT>
