<HEADLINE> Steel Plant to Stop Raising Output for Environment (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China has maintained the world's highest economic growth for
several years, but problems like resources depletion and
environmental deterioration are also looming large in this most
populous country in the world.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Xiaoke, another NPC deputy who is an executive council
member of the Chinese Society of Environmental Science, said that
environmental problems, if not handled timely and properly, could
do serious harm to China's reform and opening-up drive.
</P>
<P>
"However, the central authorities have shown great resolution
and taken really fast action in environmental protection in recent
years. I did'nt quite expect that," she said.
</P>
<P>
According to Bi, Capital Steel last year spent 100 million yuan
(about 12 million US dollars) fighting pollution, something quite
unthinkable a few years ago.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing today, drivers have been required to use unleaded
gas, natural gas from northwest China is replacing coal as the
city's main fuel, and residents can see weekly air quality reports
released by the municipal government through the local media.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin said that the city would seek new
economic growth mainly from the hi-tech sectors, and that the
municipal government would force all local enterprises to adopt
the strategy of sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has ordered all industrial enterprises
across the country to either meet state standards for pollution
control before 2000 or get closed. By the end of 1997, more than
60,000 enterprises had been shut down for causing serious
pollution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
