top legislature, with a hope that China will still be stable
politically and prosperous economically and have a still
higher-degree of democracy.
</P>
<P>
One of these messages was brought back by Su Xiaoqing, a
teacher from Guizhou Medical College and currently a visiting
scholar of entomological biology in North Carolina University in
the past two and half months.
</P>
<P>
"On February 18, I was informed by my husband through e-mail
that I was elected deputy of the National People's Congress
(NPC)," said Su, who immemdiately hurried to Beijing from the US
for the current session.
