Resistance Party (Renamo) has condemned the Mozambican government
for fraudulent practices and asked the voting to be undertaken in
June or July this year.
</P>
<P>
Other parties have also registered for the elections, but they
demanded Thursday that the elections be held on June 30th, so
that the government could correct the mistakes in voters
registration.  
