<HEADLINE> Weekly Report on Kuala Lumpur Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 7 (Xinhua) -- The Kuala Lumpur Stock
Exchange (KLSE) was on a downtrend this week with the benchmark
100-bluechips stock Composite Index (CI) losing 55.0 points for
the news that four Malaysian bank and financial institutions need
recapitalization.
</P>
<P>
The CI ended the week at 690.36 points, the all-share Emas
Index dropped 14.71 points to 176.55 while the Industrial Index
sagged 70.64 points to 1,274.35.
</P>
<P>
On the KLSE, the main board turnover this week decreased to
1.414 billion shares valued at 3.449 billion ringgit (about 0.88
billion U.S. dollars) from last week's 2.280 billion shares valued
at 5.125 billion ringgit (about 1.314 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Second Board volume this week declined to 170.453 million
shares valued at 487.782 million ringgit (about 125.072 million
U.S. dollars) from 220.142 million shares valued at 689.142
million ringgit (about 176.703 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover fell to 36.744 million shares valued at
191.911 million ringgit (about 49.208 million U.S. dollars) from
66.676 million shares valued at 273.777 million ringgit (about
70.199 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
