<HEADLINE> Vietnam Lose Their Third Foreign Coach in Two Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam lost their third foreign
coach in two years after Colin Murphy resigned from the position,
an official said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Murphy, who is currently holidaying in Britain, resigned for
"personal reasons," the federation official said.
</P>
<P>
"His contract expired in November. The two sides were unable to
agree on an extension until end 1998," he added.
</P>
<P>
Trade union daily Lao Dong said Saturday that Murphy had asked
for 7,000 dollars a month in his new contract but that the
federation would have rejected it.
</P>
<P>
Murphy was taken on last July after German Karl Heinz Weigang
and Brazilian Edson Araujo left following differences with
Vietnamese sports authorities.
</P>
<P>
They had complained of lack of cooperation from the
authorities, poor living and working conditions. 
</P>
