<HEADLINE> Street Cleaning Bidding in Shanghai's Pudong Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 7 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area, a booming
economic powerhouse in Shanghai, is inviting bidding for a street
cleaning company to take charge of the seven km-long Dongfang
Boulevard.
</P>
<P>
A dozen of licensed companies, both state-owned and
privately-owned, have given bids to compete with cleaning squads
in local environment department, which used to take on all the
street cleaning duties in the city.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 226 of the 329 streets in Pudong are now
of business for the environment department, and the remaining 103
streets totaling a space of 540 sq.m. are being maintained by
these street cleaning companies.
</P>
<P>
Their participation has spurred a market competition mechanism
into the city's environmental protection field. 
</P>
