<HEADLINE> Figures from China's Draft Plan for 1998 Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Following are major figures from a
draft plan for China's national economic and social development in
1998, submitted by Minister in charge of the State Planning
Commission Chen Jinhua at the ongoing First Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress on Friday:
</P>
<P>
-- Main macro-control targets for 1998 are: economic growth
rate eight percent; investment in fixed assets to increase by 10
percent or more; rise in retail prices confined to three percent
and rise in consumer prices to about five percent; deficit reduced
by 10 billion yuan to 46 billion yuan; total volume of currency to
be issued 150 billion yuan; total imports and exports 345 billion
US dollars; natural population growth rate controlled below 1.06
percent; registered unemployment rate about 3.5 percent in cities
and towns;
</P>
<P>
-- Total grain output 492.5 million tons; total cotton output
four million tons; output of oil-bearing crops 23 million tons;
sugar crops 87 million tons; meat 56.5 million tons; aquatic
products 38 million tons; number of poor people in rural
population reduced to below 40 million;
</P>
<P>
-- Projected output of major industrial products in 1998 are:
raw coal 1.42 billion tons; crude oil 157 million tons; natural
gas 20.4 billion cubic meters; electricity 1.2 trillion kwh; steel
107 million tons; ethylene 3.8 million tons; chemical fertilizers
29 million tons (calculated on the basis of active ingredients);
chemical fibers 4.2 million tons; motor vehicles 1.65 million;
integrated circuits 2.5 billion pieces; and digital
program-controlled telephone lines 25 million;
</P>
<P>
-- Fixed asset investment 2.785 trillion yuan, including 1.050
trillion yuan for capital construction, 470 billion yuan for
technological upgrading and 355 billion yuan for real estate
development;
</P>
<P>
-- Newly-added production capacities: new railways 941
kilometers; double-track railways 385 kilometers; electrified
railways 980 kilometers; expressways 820 kilometers; crude oil
7.12 million tons; power-generating capacity 11.84 million kw;
handling capacity of ports 8.35 million tons; and long-distance
optical cable 50,000 sheath kilometers;
</P>
<P>
-- Radio coverage to reach 86.2 percent and TV coverage 88
percent of the population; that
</P>
<P>
-- Per capita disposable income of urban residents and that of
rural people to rise by about four percent in real terms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
