<HEADLINE> Observation of NPC &AMP; CPPCC: Central Authorities' Ability of Commanding Overall Situation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Central collective leadership is
fully capable of commending the overall situation in China and
leading the people across the country to attain its cross-century
blueprint for development.
</P>
<P>
The consensus was reached by deputies to the Ninth National
People's Congress (NPC) First Session in their panel discussions
on Premier Li Peng's government work report delivered on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
On the previous successful and fruitful five-year term, they
cited it as an "extraordinary period", which have laid a solid
foundation for accomplishing the goals set for China's Ninth
Five-Year Plan and its long-range development objective for the
year 2010" and said it would be recorded in the annals of the
Chinese history".
</P>
<P>
Deputies from across China attributed the decisive factor for
China's successes during this period to the correct leadership of
the Party Central Committee and the State Council and their
capability to commend the overall situation.
</P>
<P>
Tian Chengping, secretary of the Qinghai Provincial Party
Committee, noted that the achievements scored over the past five
years, especially a number of big events occurred in 1997, show
the policy decisions made by the central authorities headed by
Jiang Zemin are correct. It proves to be a matured, staunch and
prestigious collective leadership.
</P>
<P>
Whether China's reform will be successful in the years ahead
hinges upon the correctly handling of relationship among reforms,
development and stability, said Wang Tao, a deputy from China's
northernmost Heilongjiang Province, who is also a senior adviser
of the China Petroleum and Natural Gas Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Lin Qinglin, secretary of the Hainan CPC Provincial Committee,
acknowledged that China maintained a "high growth rate" and "low
inflation" with a "soft landing". The reason behind the success
should go to the farsightedness of the Party Central Committee as
well as matroeconomic control policies it has introduced to China's
economic field.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi Provincial Governor Shu Shengyou, Jiangsu Provincial
Party Secretary Chen Huanyou and a number of other deputies hold
that the third generation of the central collective leadership
acquired a deep understanding of China's specific conditions,
successfully experimented with Deng Xiaoping Theory and gained an
initiative in acute competitions.
</P>
