<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: "Further Progress Under Stable Conditions" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Following is an explanation for
the term "further progress under stable conditions" mentioned in
Premier Li Peng's government work report to the Ninth National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
"Further Progress under stable conditions" is a principle
policy adopted by the Chinese government in formulating
macro-economic policies over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
The Central Economic Conference, held at the end of 1997,
stated that China would continue to implement the principle of
"Further progress under stable conditions" in the economic field
this year.
</P>
<P>
Stabilization refers to practising a moderately tight financial
and monetary policy, curtailing inflation, promoting
agricultural development, preventing and eliminating financial
risks, promoting social security system and maintaining a
macro-economic and social environment.
</P>
<P>
To achieve an advancement, China must make a breakthrough in
the reforms of state-owned enterprises, financial systems and
other aspects.
</P>
<P>
The country will make progress in economic restructuring,
draw up measures to solve key social problems, raise the level
of opening to the outside world and improve the quality and
efficiency of the national economy as a whole.
</P>
<P>
On the premise that China is to maintain a fairly rapid
economic growth. Stabilization and advancement completement and
promote each other. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980307.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Large and All-Inclusive, Small and All-Inclusive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Following is an explanation for
the term "Large and all-inclusive, small and all-inclusive"
mentioned in Premier Li Peng's government work report to the Ninth
National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Under China's planned economic system in the past, all
localities blindly sought to build an industrial structure that
is inclusive of all products, and all businesses sought to have
the capability to perform all social functions.
</P>
<P>
As a result of this practice, much investment was put into
similar projects and facilities unnecessarily, resulting in a
serious waste of resources and funds.
</P>
<P>
In his government work report delivered at the Fifth Session
 of the Eighth National People's Congress, Premier Li Peng suggested
that greater efforts be made to adjust the industrial structure
to solve this long-standing problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
