<HEADLINE> More Than 700,000 Tourists Visit Thailand in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Thailand received in January
703,741 tourists from all over the world, who brought to the
country about 26 billion baht (604 million US dollars), the Nation
newspaper said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Despite a significant drop in tourist arrivals from South
Korea, Indonesia and Japan, the number of tourists visiting the
country in January jumped by 13.62 percent from the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
More tourists from Eastern Europe and the Middle East should be
attributed to the sharp rise.
</P>
<P>
The government has projected a seven percent growth in tourist
arrivals this year, or a total of 7.72 million. It also expects
that spending per person will rise due to the weakness of the
baht.
</P>
<P>
According to the National Economic and Social Development
Board, this year's target is to generate 272 billion baht (6.05
billion US dollars), up from last year's 233 billion baht (5.2
billion dollars). 
</P>
