<HEADLINE> Figures for China's Economic &AMP; Social Development in 1997 (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Following are main figures in a
report on the implementation of the 1997 Plan for National
Economic and Social Development delivered yesterday by Chen
Jinhua, minister in charge of the State Planning Commission, at
the ongoing First Session of the Ninth National People's Congress
(NPC):
</P>
<P>
-- In 1997 China's Gross Domestic Product reached 7.4772
trillion yuan, an increase of 8.8 percent over the previous year.
The primary industry grew by 3.5 percent, secondary industry 10.8
percent and tertiary industry 8.2 percent;
</P>
<P>
-- Retail prices rose by 0.8 percent, representing a drop of
5.3 percentage points from 1996, and consumer prices rose by 2.8
percent, 5.5 percentage points less than the figure for the
previous year;
</P>
<P>
-- Grain output reached 492.5 million tons; cotton output was
4.3 million tons; the total output of meat came to 53.54 million
tons and aquatic products to 35.61 million tons; the added-value
of township and village enterprises reached 1.8 trillion yuan;
</P>
<P>
-- The production of standard coal reached 1.34 billion tons;
power-generating capacity increased by 13.76 million kw;
newly-built railways opened to traffic in 1997 totaled 896
kilometers, electrified railways, 1,916 kilometers and
double-track railways, 551 kilometers; a total of 35,000
kilometers of new roads were added, including 1,313 kilometers of
expressways; the volume of freight handled by coastal ports
reached 878 million tons, including 9.29 million standard
containers, an increase of 30 percent over the previous year;
total passenger and freight transport in civil aviation rose by
7.5 percent; the total length of long-distance optical cable
installed increased by 27,000 sheath kilometers, that of digital
microwave links by 14,400 kilometers and the number of telephone
lines by 19.61 million; the number of mobile telephone users
reached 13.23 million;
</P>
<P>
-- Money supply increased by 17.3 percent; money put into
circulation in 1997 amounted to 137.6 billion yuan; total savings
deposits in all financial institutions increased by 1.294 trillion
yuan, an increase of 18.6 percent over the previous year; loans
rose by 1.0703 trillion yuan, an increase of 16.7 percent; foreign
exchange reserves reached 139.9 billion US dollars at the end of
1997, an increase of 34.9 billion US dollars over the figure at
the beginning of the year;
</P>
