<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Solution to the dead-locked deal
of Thailand's purchase of eight F/A 18 jet fighters from the
United States is expected to be settled during Prime Minister
Chuan Leekpai's visit to the US next week, the Bangkok Post quoted
a senior official as saying Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Kobsak Chutikul said that Thai and
US officials agreed in preparatory talks in Washington earlier
this week that "there must be a solution to the issue."
</P>
