Officials offered three options for the five F/A jet fighters:
finding a third country to buy the planes, extending period of
payment or having the US take the planes back for the use of its
own armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Cash-strapped Thailand can no longer afford to spend some 18
billion baht (409 million US dollars) on the eight fighter planes
it earlier ordered.
</P>
<P>
The pentagon had made clear that the matter would have to be
discussed by Prime Minister Chuan, who is also defense minister of
Thailand, and President Clinton during their meeting scheduled for
March 13. 
