the United States between March 11 to 17, during which he will
hold talks with US President Bill Clinton and travel to New York
and Los Angeles to meet US businessmen as well as Thai nationals.
</P>
<P>
Soros, who is chief executive of the Quantum Fund, has been
blamed by some ASEAN politicians for sparking Asia's crisis by
speculating on regional currencies and stampeding investors into a
sell-off.
</P>
<P>
Media reports in Bangkok on Wednesday said Soros was
considering investing in Thailand by pumping 650 million dollars
into the country's Nakornthai Strip Mill Plc.
</P>
