<HEADLINE> Chilean President Accepts Ministry's Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei
has accepted Planning and Cooperation Minister Roberto Pizarro's
resignation, Government General Secretary Jose Joaquin Brunner
confirmed here Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, Brunner said he could not know the reason for which
Pizarro resigned.
</P>
<P>
"The president does not comment about this kind of
conversations he has directly with his ministers," said Brunner.
</P>
<P>
Pizarro announced Thursday his decision on the resignation, but
has refused to reveal the cause of his resignation. 
