<HEADLINE> Rafter, Rusedski Blitzed Out in Rotterdam Indoors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Patrick Rafter of
Australia and third seed Britain's Greg Rusedski were blitzed by
home players in Friday's quarter-finals of the 725,000
U.S. dollars World Indoor tournament in Rotterdam, Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, last year's U.S. Open champion, was upset 6-4, 6-4 by
Jan Siemerink, and Rusedski was beaten by fifth-seeded Richard
Krajicek 3-6, 7-6 (7-2), 7-6 (7-3).
</P>
<P>
In other two quarter-finals, Brett Steven of New Zealand
defeated Tomas Carbonell of Spain 4-6, 7-6 (7-5), 7-5, and Thomas
Johansson of Sweden edged 7-6 (10-8), 6-2, Johan Van Herck of
Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Rafter was broken in the fifth game of the first set and lost
the set 6-4 to his 48th-ranked left-handed opponent, who beat
Croat Goran Ivanisevic in the first round.
</P>
<P>
The Australian, ranked third in the world, lost his serve again
in the seventh game of the second set on the fourth breakpoint.
</P>
</TEXT>
