<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Efes Beats Cibona in Euro Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Efes roared back from a 12-point
deficit to beat Cibona Zagreb in their European Cup quarter-final
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Efes went through as it also won the first leg in front of its
fanatical home crowd 75-59.
</P>
<P>
Cibona built a healthy 40-28 lead in the first half after
leading by as much as 14 poitns thanks to some good defending and
long range shooting.
</P>
<P>
Efes came back strongly in the second half, starting 8-0.
Their top scorer with 26 points, Ufuk Sarica, dominated this part
of the game, keeping the Istanbul team in touch with Cibona.
</P>
<P>
Some sloppy attacking cost Cibona dearly towards the end of the
regular play, with Efes' American forward Brain Howard sinking one
of his two free throws for a 65-65 tie and the first overtime.
</P>
<P>
Efes' playmaker, diminutive Macedonian Petar Naumoski, stepped
in to take charge but his counterpart, Damir Mulaomerovic, scored
three points seconds from time for 76-76 and the second overtime.
</P>
<P>
Efes again built a four-point lead but young Cibona centre
Sandro Nicevic, coming from the bench for fouled-out veteran
Dzevad Alihodzic, equalised from the free-throw line for 85-85,
missing a chance to seal the game in the final second.
</P>
<P>
By the time the game entered the third overtime, Efes had their
best players Naumoski and Sarica sidelined for collecting five
fouls each but Cibona failed to capitalise.
</P>
<P>
Murat Evlyaoglu took control by scoring important points,
including a three-point jumper from seven metres for a six-point
lead that destroyed Cibona's hopes.
</P>
<P>
Cibona's American pointguard Kenneth Atkins scored on the break
to bring his team within reach at 98-100 with some 10 seconds
remaining.
</P>
<P>
He then grabbed the ball under the basket just as it was thrown
back into the field, but then missed an easy lay-up for the
equaliser.
</P>
<P>
The Turks broke away and centre Mirsad Turkcan slam-dunked
unchallenged for the final 102-98 and a place in the
quarterfinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
