<HEADLINE> Cuba, Surinam Sign Public Health Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Cuba and Surinam signed here Friday
a letter of intention on public health that opens the door wider
to bilateral assistance between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement of cooperation in this area has been the first of
its kind between the two countries. It was signed by public
health ministers Carlos Dotres of Cuba and Theodore Vishnudatt of
Surinam, who is in Cuba on a visit.
</P>
<P>
The agreement covers medical sciences, transfer of technology,
training of personnel, technical assistance and counseling, and
the establishment and modernization of laboratories. 
