<HEADLINE> Klinsmann to Leave Spurs at End of Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Juergen Klinsmann announced on
Friday he will leave Tottenham Spurs at the end of the season due
to his row with coach Christian Gross.
</P>
<P>
Klinsmann had a tunnel bust-up with Gross after last week's 1-0
win over Bolton.
</P>
<P>
The veteran German captain, who has capped 100 times, announced
earlier this year that he is to quit international soccer after
the World Cup.
</P>
<P>
But the German promised to play his best in the remaining
season when the Premiership club is struggling to avoid relegation.
</P>
<P>
Klinsmann, who has the reputation as speaking out his mind,
ended his previous spell at Tottenham in May 1995 with a row with
chairman Alan Sugar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
