<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 7 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Philippine newspapers Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- A Saudi Arabian Airline jet plane bound for Riyadh was
forced to return to Ninoy Aquino International Airport in Manila
Friday because of a bomb threat which turned out to be false.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Times
</P>
<P>
-- The Commission on Election of the Philippines has failed so
far to set up a mechanism to monitor over-spending by candidates
in the May national elections, raising fears that the coming polls
would turn out to be the most expensive in recent history.
</P>
<P>
Manila Standard
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Fidel Ramos Saturday denied in the
strongest terms possible authorship of a supposed letter to
Finance Secretary Salvador Enriquez, bearing his signature and
soliciting financial support for his administration party in
election campaigns.
</P>
<P>
Malaya
</P>
<P>
-- After 34 trips abroad, President Ramos will leave again in
April, and this time he is getting what he has long wanted and
waited for: a state visit to the United States.  
</P>
