<HEADLINE> Anti-doping Panel Seeks More Governmental Coordanation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- An anti-doping panel set up by
world swimming governing body FINA discussed about more
coordination with governments at its first meeting on Friday in
Lausanne, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The FINA Task Force, which was established on Juanuary 10,
wished a marriage of power between sports and governments would
help to eliminate doping not just from swimming, but from all
sport.
</P>
<P>
The Task Force, comprising scientises and anti-doping experts
from seven nations, assorted to research priorities, educational
campaign and improving coordiantion between sports organisations
and governments in fighting against drug. 
</P>
</TEXT>
