<HEADLINE> Bartova Sets World Indoor Record in Women's Pole Vault </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Daniela Bartova of the Czech
Republic set a new indoor pole vault world record here Friday when
she soared over at four meters and 46 centimeters.
</P>
<P>
The former world record of 4.45 meters was set by Anzhela
Balakhonova of the Ukraine at the European Indoor Championships in
Valencia on March 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
