<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Share prices turned higher on the
New York Stock Exchange Friday, with the Dow Jones industrial
average gaining 125.06 points to close at 8,569.39.
</P>
<P>
The 30 stock benchmark index recovered most of the losses in
the past two days, but is still some 15 points away from Tuesday's
record close of 8,584.83.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed the market performance Friday mainly to a
government report on a 4.6 percent unemployment rate for February,
which was a 24 year low. The figure boosted investors' confidence
in the country's economy.
</P>
<P>
Reports of lower first quarter earning and profit estimates by
some big corporations such as Intel and Motorola pushed the Dow
down Wednesday and Thursday, after a bull run since February.
</P>
<P>
According to preliminary figures, advancing issues led
decliners 3-1 Friday, with trading volume up to 663.54 million
shares from 650.66 million shares Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Other indexes also gained.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 stock list rose 20.59 to 1,055.64,
and the NYSE composite index was up 9.33 to 549.64. The technology
heavy Nastaq composite index, which suffered the most previously,
rose 41.57 to 1,753.49.
</P>
<P>
On the smaller companies' line, the Russell 2000 index rose
6.90 to 463.72 and the American Stock Exchange composite index
rose 8.57 to 712.91. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
