<HEADLINE> Security Council Urges Croatian Government to Commit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Council called upon the Croatian Government to reaffirm and
by its actions to demonstrate its commitment to fulfilling its
obligations under the Basic Agreement and other agreements in
full, including through progress on national reconciliation at
every level.
</P>
<P>
The Council also urged the Croatia Government to take prompt
and unequivocal steps to ensure the safety, security and rights of
all Croatian citizens and to build confidence among the Serb
community throughout Croatia by providing promised funding for the
Joint Council of Municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The Council stressed these steps should include measures to
create the conditions to allow local serbs to remain in the
region, to facilitate the return of refugees and displaced
persons and to address underlying practical and economic issues
which inhibit returns.
</P>
<P>
Recognizing that the performance of the Croatian police has
been generally satisfactory, the Council noted that public
confidence in the police is slow. It called on the Croatian
Government to take measures to improve public confidence in the
police as part of a wider program of measures to prevent
ethnically-motivated crime and ensure the protection and equal
treatment of all Croatian citizens, regardless of ethnicity.
</P>
