<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Grants Aid for Civil Society Development in Belarus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
European Union (EU)'s executive body, Friday approved 5 million
ECUs (some 6 million U.S. dollars) in aid for civil society
development in Belarus.
</P>
<P>
The so-called Tacis program, which the commission adopted
Friday in Brussels, will provide support to three hey target
groups -- non-governmental organizations (NGOs), the media and the
education sector.
</P>
<P>
The commission said in a statement that it would use nearly
half of the aid to strengthen the institutional capacity of
Belarusian NGOs and enhance public awareness of democratic issues
by targeting more than 30 NGOs in the whole Belarusian territory
to develop their capacity through different activities.
</P>
<P>
The media support program aims to address the needs of
independent Belarusian journalists by providing them with training
and know-how designed to strengthen their professional abilities
as well as to open local media to the experiences of counterpart
organizations in other European states.
</P>
<P>
Another program, called the Institutional Twinning Program,
aims to support east-west cooperation of institutes providing
education and training to the younger generations.
</P>
<P>
"The younger generations are the future of Belarus and should
therefore be facilitated in the learning of principles and values
that govern an open democracy," the commission said in the
statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
