<HEADLINE> UNDP Promises Full Potential for Women as Equal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) will continue to take firm actions to
advance and enable women to realize their full potential as equal,
indeed critical, partners in development, UNDP Administrator James
Gustave Speth said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion of commemorating International Women's
Day, Speth said this is an opportunity to remind the world that
human rights cannot be attained without the rights of women to
equal employment, education, health and freedom from abuse.
</P>
<P>
Speth said the support for sustainable human development is
directed toward decent living standard and human dignity through
the realization of all human rights -- economic, social, cultural,
civil and political.
</P>
<P>
He said these rights are invisible and ally equally to all, and
they specifically include the right of women everywhere to live in
equal terms with men.
</P>
<P>
The administrator said at UNDP, firm actions have been taken to
advance women throughout ranks, both at the Headquarters and at
the country level, through the introduction of measures to build a
more gender sensitive and enabling work environment.
</P>
<P>
Speth said commitment has also been made to bring gender
consideration into the mainstream of the organization's work at
the Headquarters and where the programs are served.
</P>
<P>
He added he has asked UNDP resident representatives to lend
their support to the preparation of country reports to the
Commission on the Elimination of All Forms of Discrimination
Against Women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
